cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a computer vision-based approach for phenotyping the distribution of epicuticular waxes on grapevine berries. The approach involves capturing illumination-separated images of the berries using a Mobile Light-Separation-Lab and using a convolutional neural network for image analysis. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for image analysis, which could also place it in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
